      <body>
         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
        
		<lg met="elegaic">
		<l n="1" met="hexameter"><w lemma="οὐδέ">Οὐδὲ</w> <w lemma="θνήσκω">θανὼν</w> <w lemma="κλέος">κλέος</w> <w lemma="ἐσθλός">ἐσθλὸν</w> <w lemma="ἀπόλλυμι">ἀπώλεσας</w> <w lemma="εἰς">ἐς</w> <w lemma="χθών">χθόνα</w> <w lemma="πᾶς">πᾶσαν</w>,</l>
		<l n="2" met="pentameter"><w lemma="ἀλλά">ἀλλ'</w> <w lemma="ἔτι">ἔτι</w> <w lemma="σός">σῆς</w> <w lemma="ψυχή">ψυχῆς</w> <w lemma="ἀγλαός">ἀγλαὰ</w> <w lemma="πᾶς">πᾶντα</w> <w lemma="μένω">μένει</w>,</l>
		<l n="3" met="hexameter"><w lemma="ὅσος">ὅσσ'</w> <w lemma="λαγχάνω">ἔλαχές</w> <w lemma="τε">τε</w> <w lemma="φύσις">φύσει</w>, <w lemma="μῆτις">μῆτιν</w> <w lemma="πανάριστος">πανάριστε</w>·</l>
		<l n="4" met="pentameter"><w lemma="ὁ">τῷ</w> <w lemma="ἄρα">ῥα</w> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="εἰς">ἐς</w> <w lemma="μάκαρ">μακάρων</w> <w lemma="νῆσος">νῆσον</w> <w lemma="βαίνω">ἔβης</w>, <persName key="Pytheas" nymRef="#Πύθεας" type="attested"><name nymRef="#Πυθέας">Πυθέα</name></persName>.</l>
		</lg>
      </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Not even after death have you lost your fine reputation in the whole earth, but still all the splendid <supplied reason="subaudible">achievements</supplied> of your soul remain - both those which you inherited, and those which you learnt, according to your nature, most excellent in intellect. So now, Pytheas, you have also gone to the Island of the Blest.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>This epigram, preserved only in the <title>Greek Anthology</title>, was very probably inscribed at Aphrodisias for Pytheas, for whom see <ref type="inscription" n="55" target="110070.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="56" target="020020.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="57" target="080610.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="58" target="050303.xml"/>, and discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="V.18" target=".xml"/>.</p>
         </div>
